        "title": "fix(edit): unwrap XML-RPC {item: {oldText, newText}} edit entries",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nUnwrap `{item: {oldText, newText}}` entries from XML-RPC array-of-structs\ntransport (reported with DeepSeek/XML-RPC paths). The wire format wraps each\narray element as `[{item: {oldText, newText}}]` instead of the canonical\n`[{oldText, newText}]`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/agents/sessions/tools/edit.ts`: Add XML-RPC unwrap logic in both\n  `prepareEditArguments` and `execute()` paths\n\n## Evidence\n\n### XML-RPC {item: ...} entry → canonical {oldText, newText}\n```\nInput:  [{item: {oldText: \"original content\", newText: \"replaced content\"}}]\nOutput: [{oldText: \"original content\", newText: \"replaced content\"}]\n```\n\n### Mixed entries (item-wrapped + canonical) both work\n```\nInput:  [{oldText: \"line one\", newText: \"LINE ONE\"}, {item: {oldText: \"line three\", newText: \"LINE THREE\"}}]\nOutput: Both edits applied correctly\n```\n\n_AI-assisted._",
